 {"id":"bd-uwax6","title":"PORT: __opendir / __closedir / __readdir / __readdir_r (glibc reserved aliases)","description":"Port the four glibc reserved-namespace aliases for the directory-iteration entry points: __opendir, __closedir, __readdir, __readdir_r. glibc emits these as both internal-use entry points and as the symbols NSS modules / libc-internal lookup paths link against. Without them, statically-linked NSS-using code fails at link time. Implementation: thin no_mangle Rust extern "C" wrappers delegating to the public opendir/closedir/readdir/readdir_r in dirent_abi. Tests open + iterate /tmp via each alias and verify it yields the same dirent stream as the public counterpart.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-26T12:51:24.296315487Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T12:55:28.227389608Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T12:55:28.225388218Z","close_reason":"shipped: __opendir / __closedir / __readdir / __readdir_r glibc reserved-namespace aliases delegating to existing public-name impls + 3 abi tests, all green","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
